
  <sn><md>### Air Quality Index (AQI)

The AQI is a tool for `reporting daily air quality` of any city or country. It tells us `how clean or polluted the air is`, and what associated health effects might be a concern for the public. The AQI focuses on *health effects* that one might experience within a few hours or days after breathing polluted air.

The AQI value runs from `0 to 500`. The ++higher the AQI value++, the ++greater is the level of air pollution++ and the greater is the health concern. For example, an ++AQI of 50++ represents `good air quality` with little potential to affect public health while an ++AQI value of 300++ represents `hazardous air quality`.
</md></sn>
