</md></sn><sn><md>#### Approved Air Quality Index (AQI) for Bangladesh

![diagram](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Nh-emon/QDoc/main/SES3/Soil%20and%20Enviromental%20Quality/resources/air-quality-dgrm10.png)

| Air quality index (AQI) Range | Category | Colour |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 0-50 | Good | Green |
| 51-100 | Moderate | Yellow Green |
| 101-150 | Caution | Yellow |
| 151-200 | Unhealthy | Orange |
| 201-300 | Very Unhealthy | Red |
| 301-500 | Extremely Unhealthy | Purple |
</md></sn><sn><md>#### Ambient National Air Quality Standards for Bangladesh Including WHO Guideline

**Air quality standard:** Air quality standards indicate the level of pollutants that can't be exceeded during a specified time period in a specified geographical area, with due reference to the method of measurement, units of measurement, concentration and time of exposure.

The ambient national air quality standards for Bangladesh including WHO guideline is given below:


![img](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Nh-emon/QDoc/main/SES3/Soil%20and%20Enviromental%20Quality/resources/Screenshot%20From%202026-07-08%2019-28-47.png)

+++ see table

| Pollutant | Bangladesh Standard | WHO Guideline | Averaging Time |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Carbon Monoxide (CO) | 10 mg/m³ (9 ppm) | 10 mg/m³ | 8 hour |
| | 40 mg/m³ (35 ppm) | 30 mg/m³ | 1 hour |
| Lead (Pb) | 0.5 µg/m³ | 0.5 µg/m³ | Annual |
| Oxides of Nitrogen (NOx) | 100 µg/m³ (0.053 ppm) | - | Annual |
| Suspended Particulate Matter (SPM) | 200 µg/m³ | - | 8 hour |
| Particulates (PM₁₀) | 50 µg/m³ (150 µg/m³) | 20 µg/m³ | Annual |
| Fine Particulates (PM₂.₅) | 15 µg/m³ (65 µg/m³) | 10 µg/m³ | Annual |
| Ozone (O₃) | 235 µg/m³ (0.12 ppm) | - | 1 hour |
| | 157 µg/m³ (0.08 ppm) | 100 µg/m³ | 8 hour |
| Sulfur dioxide (SO₂) | 80 µg/m³ (0.03 ppm) | - | Annual |
| | 365 µg/m³ (0.14 ppm) | 20 µg/m³ | 24 hour |

